org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.query.aggregate

Class BinningAggregation<P extends Persistable,R,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.query.aggregate.BinningAggregation<P,R,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - The configuration parameters of the inner aggregation.
    R - The type of the result that is returned by the inner aggregation.
    T - The type of the data given to the aggregation.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Persistable, Aggregation<BinningAggregationOptions<P,T>,Map<ByteArray,R>,T>

    public class BinningAggregation<P extends Persistable,R,T>
extends Object
implements Aggregation<BinningAggregationOptions<P,T>,Map<ByteArray,R>,T>
    A Meta-Aggregation, to be used internally by an aggregation query.

    This takes an aggregation-supplier and a binning strategy. When new data is aggregated, it is binned, and if that bin does not exist, a new one will be made, along with a new aggregation.

    See AggregationQueryBuilder.buildWithBinningStrategy(BinningStrategy, int) AggregationQueryBuilder#bin} for usage

      • BinningAggregation

        public BinningAggregation(Aggregation<P,R,T> baseAggregation,
                          BinningStrategy binningStrategy,
                          int maxBins)
        Creates a BinningAggregation based upon a base aggregation and a strategy for binning.
        Parameters:
        baseAggregation - A supplier of the inner aggregation. This decides what is done to the data inside of the bin. Make sure that the given aggregation properly implements Aggregation#fromBinary Aggregation#toBinary.
        binningStrategy - How to bin the given data.
        maxBins - The maximum amount of bins that this aggregation should support. If a bin is computed after reaching the max, it will be silently dropped.
